@damienmg @philwo

Execute this command to locate the Tensorflow Models in your Tensorflow python environment,
```
import os; 
import inspect; 
import tensorflow; print(os.path.dirname(inspect.getfile(tensorflow)))
```

Will give you the directory for the models.

@Randolph-zeng you shouldn't use cuDNN 6.0, according to TensorFlow requirements only 5.1 is supported on Windows.
For more information please see:
https://www.tensorflow.org/install/install_windows#requirements_to_run_tensorflow_with_gpu_support

